text:
{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric hyperscooter, inspired by Mad Max style, with the following features: a large flat deck embedded with a 144V 20Ah battery, dual front and rear hydraulic suspension, and a floating rider seat suspended above the deck on its own shock absorbers like a truck or bus driver's seat. The vehicle has fat tires for stability, an aggressive aerodynamic front, and an armored rider wearing full black gear and helmet. The scooter has a rugged, high-performance design suitable for urban or off-road use. Background is a highway with some greenery.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric scooter with a long 1800mm wheelbase, large 20-inch rugged tires on both front and rear wheels, and a flat wide deck housing a massive 144V 200Ah battery. The deck includes foot pegs for leg extension and support, similar to motorcycle-style footrests. The seat is mounted independently on a floating suspension system, like a truck or bus driver’s seat, separated from the deck. The scooter has dual front and rear hydraulic suspensions, a strong tubular frame, and a sleek orange and black color scheme. It is parked on an urban pavement with green trees in the background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric scooter with a long wheelbase of 1800mm, 20-inch tires front and rear, and a large orange and black deck containing a 144V 200Ah battery. The scooter includes a front aerodynamic fairing (cowl) and an adjustable windshield integrated into the design. The rider's seat is isolated with its own suspension system like a truck or bus driver's seat. Pegs are visible on the deck for the rider’s feet. The vehicle is parked on pavement near a concrete barrier with greenery in the background. The design resembles a high-performance hyper scooter or ultra e-bike.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric hyper-scooter parked on pavement, designed with a low, step-through frame and 144V 200Ah battery embedded in the flat deck. The scooter features dual 20-inch wide wheels, front and rear suspension, and a sleek aerodynamic front fairing (cowl) and windscreen. The foot deck remains flat and extended with side pegs for foot support. The scooter has no rider, and the overall build is low-slung and performance-oriented. Background includes concrete and soft greenery, lighting is natural and clear.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution side view of a futuristic electric scooter with a rugged design and advanced mechanical structure. The scooter features a bright orange front fairing with an aerodynamic windshield, large 20-inch wheels, and a long 1800mm wheelbase. The battery pack is clearly labeled '144V 200Ah' and is mounted low along the step-through deck. The rear suspension is NOT connected to the seat; instead, it uses a separate pivoting subframe attached to the battery pack like a swingarm. The seat itself is mounted on a tall, independent post with built-in suspension, similar to a bus driver's seat, offering vertical shock absorption. The scooter is parked against a plain gray wall, emphasizing its unique mechanical design.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution image of a futuristic electric scooter without a rider, featuring a sleek matte black body and an ergonomic high-back cushioned seat mounted on an independent suspension subframe. The scooter has a visible 144V 200Ah battery box labeled on the side, a large windshield and front fairing, and dual rear shocks mounted to a pivoting subframe, not the seat. The background shows a neutral concrete wall and asphalt ground. No people or riders are present.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution concept image of a futuristic electric scooter designed with a step-through frame. It features a sleek black and orange color scheme, a large 144V 200Ah battery integrated cleanly into the low deck (not bulging), and dual 20-inch wide tires for both front and rear. The scooter includes a front aerodynamic fairing and windshield, and a fully independent floating seat resembling a bus driver's air-suspension seat. The rear shock absorbers are pivoted on a separate subframe independent from the seat. No rider is present in the image. The design emphasizes comfort, modularity, and futuristic urban mobility. Captured against a clean, minimal background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution electric hyper-scooter design with triple suspension. The seat is mounted on its own independent suspension frame (like a bus driver seat), clearly separated from the rear wheel. The rear wheel is positioned behind the seat, connected by a visible swingarm with dual shocks. The orange and black battery box (144V) is mounted low on a step-through frame. The scooter features wide 20-inch tires on both ends, a sleek aerodynamic front fairing with a clear windscreen, and ergonomic footpegs. The entire design emphasizes extreme riding comfort and structural clarity, shown in bright daylight on clean pavement with a plain concrete wall backdrop. No rider or human is present.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution digital photograph of a futuristic electric hyper scooter. The scooter has an orange battery pack labeled '144V' centrally located under the seat. The seat is a high-backed ergonomic design mounted on a floating suspension system for maximum comfort, positioned directly over the center of the battery pack. The rear wheel is extended 50mm backward from the previous position, creating a more elongated wheelbase. The frame features a step-through design with a flat foot deck, front and rear hydraulic suspension systems, and both wheels are wide 20-inch types. The background is a clean concrete wall with sparse greenery, and the lighting is soft daylight.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution electric scooter with a matte black and orange frame. It features a large 144V 200Ah battery integrated into the center deck, a thick but lowered suspension seat with backrest (now 200mm lower than standard), dual rear shocks, and 20-inch wheels. The seat is aligned with the center of the battery, and the rear wheel is shifted 50mm backward. Set against a neutral indoor studio background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A clean technical side-view diagram (blueprint style) of an electric scooter with a triple suspension system. The drawing shows detailed labeled components. The front and rear wheels are both 20 inches with visible hydraulic suspension forks. The battery pack (144V 200Ah) is mounted low and centered under the wide deck. The rider seat is mounted above the battery pack with its own independent suspension (spring or air shock absorber). The rear wheel is positioned behind the seat, with a swingarm and separate rear suspension. The image includes arrows or dotted lines showing the flow of vibration absorption: first through the wheels, then the chassis, and finally the suspended seat. The entire diagram has a technical blueprint look on a light grid background. No human figures.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A clean, high-resolution side-view technical diagram of an advanced electric scooter designed with a TSS-3 triple suspension seat system. The illustration clearly labels major components: an enlarged and extended orange battery pack running under the entire floorboard and partially under the seat; a front suspension fork on the large 20-inch front wheel; an independent rear swingarm suspension attached behind the battery; and a floating seat with its own spring suspension mounted above the battery on a separate subframe. The scooter is placed against a neutral grey background with clean outlines and labeled parts: 'Front Suspension', 'Rear Swingarm Suspension', 'Seat Suspension', 'Battery', and 'Subframe'.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical side-view diagram of an electric scooter with a long, low-profile battery pack that runs the full length of the floorboard, stretching from the front wheel area to the rear wheel. The scooter features a triple suspension system: front suspension, rear swingarm suspension, and an independently suspended ergonomic seat. The seat is mounted above the battery on a dedicated subframe, not touching the swingarm. Labels indicate 'Front Suspension,' 'Extended Floor Battery,' 'Seat Suspension,' and 'Rear Suspension'. Minimalist gray background with clean, outlined components.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution side view technical illustration of an advanced electric scooter with a rider seated, showcasing perfect ergonomic balance. The battery is fully embedded in the flat lower deck, stretched from front to rear wheel (144V 200Ah capacity). The seat is centrally mounted over the battery, slightly forward, supported by a dedicated air suspension. The rear wheel is supported by an independent swingarm and suspension, not connected to the seat. The front fork features long-travel suspension. The rider is in a relaxed, upright position, knees bent at a natural angle, hands comfortably on the handlebars, with feet resting on forward foot pegs. The image is labeled and presented on a clean grey background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A clean, high-quality digital side-view diagram of an electric scooter featuring a triple suspension system with a human rider. The scooter is black and orange. The seat suspension is visibly separated from the rear wheel suspension. The rear wheel axle is placed 150mm behind the rider's hip line. Labels indicate 'Front Suspension', 'Seat Suspension', and 'Rear Suspension'. The battery labeled '144V 200Ah' is flat and extends under the rider. The rider sits comfortably with a natural forward-leaning posture and knees slightly bent. The diagram uses a neutral background and clean vector lines.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
